/r/AdvancedRunning - An analysis of race reports


What is /r/AdvancedRunning?

/r/AdvancedRunning is an online forum “for runners who love the sport of running and all its aspects”.
The prefix Advanced does not refer the speed of the runner. There is no required pace or distance to join in on the discussion at /r/advancedrunning, only the love of the sport and aspect of running.
But… how fast is Advanced really?

What is a race report?

Race reports are own accounts of races, where runners describe their training, goals for the race, how the race went, etc.

The Data

Race details

When does /r/advancedrunning race?

AdvancedRunners race mostly in the Spring (from March to May) and in Autumn (October and November), when conditions are better for racing. Of course, most races are held in these months, so runners are also more likely to chose these months for their races.

How fast is /r/advancedrunning?

Standing out above all other times, a marathon time between 02:55:00 and 03:00:00 is the most common race time. Running a marathon under 3 hours is a very common goal for advanced runners. 3 hours is a round number, a very challenging time, and in addition, it’s about the time needed to be able to qualify for the Boston Marathon. 15 people have run below 02:35. The distribution has a long right tail, but not may runners go over 4 hours for their marathons.
